name: NPR
text: President-elect Joe Biden is set to give remarks to the American people at 8 p.m. ET. Watch live here: https://t.co/0yO9tGCyyu

name: NPR
text: Slovenian Prime Minister Janez Janša, an anti-immigrant conservative, attacked the media for declaring a Biden win. Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán also did not congratulate Biden on Saturday. https://t.co/pjuAPqoK94

name: NPR
text: Unlike President Trump, who is chummy with the British prime minister, President-elect Joe Biden is no fan of Boris Johnson. https://t.co/pqze9tA8nU

name: NPR
text: Crowds poured into the streets of the city that had gripped the nation's attention for days as Pennsylvania counted the ballots that tipped the presidential election in Biden's favor. https://t.co/xz9LZIwG39

name: NPR
text: Outside the Chase Center in Wilmington, Del., Vice President-elect Kamala Harris thanked Democratic supporters, campaign staff and poll workers. "You ushered in a new day for America," she said. https://t.co/OgzIyHuBX4

name: NPR
text: Statements poured in congratulating Joe Biden on his victory in the 2020 election — including from Trump's global allies. Iranian and Palestinian leaders expressed relief at the president's loss. https://t.co/0ah4w0lIk1

name: NPR
text: A long tradition of presidential pets will be revived in January. And a little history will be made, too: President-elect Joe Biden's younger dog will be the first rescue dog in the White House. https://t.co/pvp3am7oop

name: NPR
text: Cándido Camero, the Cuban percussionist who brought the rhythms of Havana to New York's jazz clubs in the 1940s, has died at age 99. https://t.co/7MedMk1gBh

name: NPR
text: Opinion: NPR's Scott Simon reflects on the record amount of money spent this campaign season, a goodly amount spent by candidates who did not win. https://t.co/92n4nNCA0X

name: NPR
text: From elation to dismay, these photos capture America's reaction to Joe Biden's victory in the presidential election. https://t.co/QwdZXuGznD

name: NPR
text: Ruby Bridges was the first Black student at her New Orleans elementary school. Now, she's written a book to tell kids her story. https://t.co/kkegJhBFCo

name: NPR
text: Linda Diaz, who won this year's Tiny Desk Contest at NPR Music, is a chess expert an international chess champion. She sat down to talk with us about the Netflix series The Queen's Gambit. https://t.co/woa103Ia2T

name: NPR
text: We really do live on a beautiful planet with beautiful people – check out these photo award winners. A contest spokeswoman said they make her “nostalgic” for the pre-pandemic world.  https://t.co/jQVo7ad0lY

name: NPR
text:
20-year-old Sabria Nawrozi won’t let Taliban opposition keep her from playing soccer. 

"I was only concentrating on my goals, and that's why I didn't have any fear." https://t.co/qIYAUSzTV6
